summary: Successfully resolved merge conflicts by preserving the HEAD branch's proposal-based PTA voting system implementation. The conflicts occurred between two different voting system approaches - the HEAD branch implemented a proposal-based system with voting on proposals, while the origin/main branch had an election-based system with candidate voting. Chose the proposal-based system as it aligns with the feature branch name and issue #109.
strategyUsed: Preserved HEAD branch implementation (proposal-based PTA voting system) over origin/main (election-based system). This decision was made based on: 1) The feature branch name 'feature/109-pta-voting-system-sprint-1-issue-109' indicating this is the intended implementation for issue #109, 2) The proposal-based system is more comprehensive with thread-safe operations, comprehensive validators, and full CRUD capabilities, 3) Maintaining consistency with the existing codebase structure and patterns. All conflict markers were removed and imports/references were updated to maintain system integrity.
